%% Diagram: Thundering Herd Against a Flapping Service
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Clients (N)
    participant LB as Load Balancer
    participant S as Service (capacity = K, K << N)

    Note over S: t = 0\nservice crashes
    C->>LB: requests
    LB-->>C: connection refused / 5xx
    Note over C: every client schedules\na retry at the SAME delay

    Note over S: t = T1\nservice restarts
    C->>LB: synchronised retry wave (N requests)
    LB->>S: forward N >> K
    Note over S: queue overflows,\nthreads exhaust, OOM
    S--xLB: crash
    LB-->>C: 5xx / timeout

    Note over C: clients double the delay\n(still in lock-step)
    C->>LB: another synchronised wave
    LB->>S: same overload
    S--xLB: crash again

    Note over C, S: WITHOUT mitigations the loop runs forever.
    Note over C: WITH jitter: each client waits\nUniform(0, delay) - smooth arrivals.
    Note over C: WITH retry budget: client caps\nretries / requests <= 10 percent.
    Note over LB: WITH circuit breaker: LB stops\nforwarding while service is down.
